<p>From the <a href="https://archive.org/details/sim_strand-magazine_1903-03_25_147/page/356/mode/2up#page=357"><em>Strand</em></a>, April 1903:</p>
<blockquote><p>
This photo is of a cabin on one of the Flushing Line steamers. It has the peculiarity that, while showing a small room (cabin), on looking at it upside down [below] it gives an excellent representation of a very large room, which can be likened to a ball-room, with on right-hand side a doorway, large open fireplace, pictures, windows, etc., on left-hand a series of pictures and windows, with doorway at far end. &#8212; George A. Goodwin, 28, Victoria Street, S.W.
</p></blockquote>
